adviseScripts.text: Isn't my daughter adorable?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: It brings a smile to my face every time I look at her, hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You have a kid?
Totally. She's adorable.
What? Of course I don't!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'm still a student.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: That's just how I refer to Tia sometimes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Hilarious that you got the wrong idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I figured you would agree.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Tia is always running up and giving me hugs, going on about how I feel like a mom to her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You take such good care of her, that you're like a father figure as well,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: so that's why I brought it up.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I hope you can continue to look after her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Naga and I have a conversation about how cute Tia is.
All the underclassmen were badgering me yesterday.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: They were wondering if I was in the graduating class because I looked old.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I hate it when they tease me for looking older.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Maybe it's because you in fact look so young, and they're just jealous.
That's terrible...
You always know what to say, Teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: And it's all the better because I know they're not just empty words.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Thanks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'm sorry,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I didn't mean to bum you out.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Don't let it get you down, okay?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Keep your chin up.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I tell Naga that age is just a number.
What do you think of this new bracelet I bought?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Did you pick it yourself? You have good taste.
It suits you well. You look mature.
What a wonderful compliment.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Keep 'em coming.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: So, in other words...
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I look old, is that it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Haha, gotcha! I'm just joking. You should have seen your face.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: We look at Naga's bracelet together.
Once in a while, I get a bit frustrated.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: At times like that, I just want to get as far away from the school as I can.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You're more than welcome to come hang out with me anytime you want.
No matter how bad you feel, you can't forget your responsibilities as a student.
I thought you'd say something like that,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: but it feels nice to hear you really say it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I might just take you up on that offer sometime.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: A truly professional answer if there ever was one. I expected no less from you, Teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: It might not be easy, but I feel like I'm back on track.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: And it's thanks to you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I speak with Naga about the difficulties of attending school.
I was wondering why everyone around me has been so glum lately,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: and it turns out exams are approaching.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: My stomach is always in knots during this time of the school year.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Have you not studied properly for your exams?
Your expression is telling me you're worried about something other than exams.
You caught me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'll take my studying more seriously from here on out.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Don't forget to cheer me on!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, you're pretty astute, Teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'm a bit worried that
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: a bunch of my friends are gonna flunk the exam.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: If that happens, then I won't be able to see them, and I don't want that...
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I share some tips with Naga on how to reduce stress during exams.
I bought another hair tie.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: It was so darned cute, that I just couldn't pass it up.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: No wonder you have so many hair ties.
Is it the one you've got on your wrist?
You know it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I've got a bunch in my bag,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: and there's a veritable mountain of them piled up in my room.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Very impressive!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: How did you realize this was the one I just bought?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You're very attentive, Teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I check out Naga's hair tie collection.
Whenever I see underclassmen talking about all their dreams,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'm not sure how to feel.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: On one hand, it's endearing, but on the other, it can be kind of sad.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Mostly endearing.
Mostly sad.
I hope they never lose that side of them,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I really do.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I can't say that
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I expected that to be your answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'm glad that you understand where I'm coming from.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Naga and I continue talking about the underclassmen.
I've seen Marciana a couple of times outside of school.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: She's quite charming.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: What makes you say that?
She's a real charmer, that's for sure.
I'm not sure.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: How should I put it...
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: She seems... very secretive.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Like she was hiding a lot from me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I see that you've already experienced that side of her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You seem awfully interested in her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'm starting to get a little envious of her!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Naga and I talk more about Marciana.
I want to correct Tia's slouching.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Whenever she sits down at her desk, she hunches over. It looks terrible.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Do you know any good ways to fix bad posture?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Let's buy her a posture correction device.
We can try to convince her to change using desserts as a reward.
Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'm not so sure that's a good idea.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I've already given her some pointers on proper posture during our breaks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: That's a great idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Tia even mentioned to me that she's a bit short on credits for desserts this month.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Thanks, Teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: As I converse with Naga, we wonder about the parts for Tia's future waist.
Teacher, what do you think about lying?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Do you think all lies are bad?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: There's nothing wrong with a little white lie.
I think all lies are bad.
You think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: What about you, Naga? What do you think?
Me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: It's a secret.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You're nothing if not firm, Teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I better watch myself from now on.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'd hate to get on your bad side.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Naga and I have a discussion about lies.
You've really got it rough, Teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You've got to care for so many Nikkes all by yourself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: That can't be an easy job.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I can't complain. It's part of my job.
It can be rough. Any chance I can have a breather?
Your professionalism is admirable,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: but rest is important too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You're not looking so hot, Teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You've got to remember to take care of yourself while you're working.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Of course.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You don't look so good anyway.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I think lying down for a bit might be a good idea.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Come, you can rest your head on my lap.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I accept Naga's suggestion and take a short rest.
Teacher, is there any chance you
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: could teach me how to refrain from impulse buying?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You bought some more accessories, didn't you?
You bought some more desserts, didn't you?
But this stud was so shiny! I absolutely had to buy it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Honestly, I must've been over 30 feet away and I could still see it twinkling.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: ... Yeah, avoiding jewelry shops for the time being might be a good idea.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Huh?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I think you've got me mixed up with Tia.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I never buy desserts on a whim.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Naga and I ponder about impulse buying and how to curb it.
When I graduate, there are two things I'll miss.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: One is not being able to see Tia every day like I do now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: What do you think the other one is?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Not being able to see your other friends?
Not being able to wear your uniform?
Sorry, but that's not it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You oughta study more, hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You're as sharp as a tack, Teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: That's correct.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Whenever I think about not being able to wear the school uniform any longer,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I get bummed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: So I'll try to enjoy it as much as possible while I still can.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Naga talking about graduation.
Teacher! Teacher!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: What is it?
I turn in the direction of Naga's shouting.
*Poke*
Hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Naga pokes me on the cheek with her finger.
I can't believe I fell for that.
What was that for?
You should see your face!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Just a moment ago, I got Tia pretty good as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Just a little prank.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: That you totally fell for! Hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Naga goes on to tell me about more of the latest pranks that are trending at school.
Among those who give off dog or cat vibes,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: which do you prefer?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Dog vibes.
Cat vibes.
So you prefer people who are more soft and cuddly?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: That's too bad.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: So you prefer people who are a bit more sassy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: That's encouraging.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Naga and I discuss whether other people around us resemble cats or dogs.
I want to add another keyring to my bag.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: What kind do you think would look best?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: A purple one shaped like a ribbon.
It doesn't look like you have room for any more keyrings.
Right! How come I didn't think of that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You clearly know what you're talking about.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for the suggestion. I'll go with this one.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: What are you talking about?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: There's plenty of space to add more.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Hurry up and pick one.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I help Naga attach the keyring to her bag.
Here, take these.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: What are they?
Some vitamins.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You've been pushing yourself hard lately.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I know it's not much, but I prepared this for you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Thank you.
Thanks, but the fact you're concerned about me is more than enough.
I'm the one who should be thankful.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You always take care of me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Take one in the morning and one at night.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Don't forget.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Please, I insist.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: If you feel I'm pressuring you, I'll take them back.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: But you better accept them next time!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I express my gratitude to Naga.
Teacher, I'm here.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: *Thud*
Naga drops her bag, which lands on the ground with a resounding thud.
What's that bag made of?
What do you have in that bag?
This bag?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Just ordinary fabric.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Is there a problem?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: You wanna see?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: *Ziiiip*
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: These are an extra pair of stockings for Tia and a spare textbook for her...
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: A backup set of gym clothes for Tia... some extra desserts for Tia...
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: This is Tia's spare tablet... oh, and then there's this...
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I watch Naga unpack her bag for what feels like forever.
No matter how much I try not to think about some unpleasant memories,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: they keep popping up.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: What would you do whenever that happens?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'd listen to soothing music and meditate.
I shout at the top of my voice to release the stress.
That's an awesome idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'll give that a try next time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Thanks, Teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, that's a funny image.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: It really cheers me up.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Thanks, Teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I comfort Naga, who seems less peppy than usual.
Whenever I do a group project,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I end up being the group leader.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: It's not like I forced anyone, either. It's all decided fair and square through a vote.
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Why do you think that happens?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: People see you as a natural-born leader.
Maybe they see you as a mature and sensible figure.
Is that what the others think of me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I'll have to continue brushing up on my leadership skills going forward then!
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: Teacher,
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: are you saying I look old?
adviseScripts.speaker: Naga

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation about group projects with Naga.
